n my fps controller experiment, I stuck with the bullet forces method to avoid the extra work of collision detection/response. I started with the character sample and made use of several collision triggers to control different behaviors (like ground detect, drop detect, stand detect), and added some fudge. I added a half-life style crouch-jump (or at least how I remember it). In most cases it behaves well as I’ve limited extreme responses, but there are some glitches like wall climbing and it d…\n  \u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFor blending animations, there’s JSandusky’s animation motion controller script.\u003c/p\u003e\u003caside class=\"onebox githubgist\" data-onebox-src=\"https://gist.github.com/JSandusky/340b09e9d104bae4c16b\"\u003e\n  \u003cheader class=\"source\"\u003e\n\n      \u003ca href=\"https://gist.github.com/JSandusky/340b09e9d104bae4c16b\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003egist.github.com\u003c/a\u003e\n  \u003c/header\u003e\n\n  \u003carticle class=\"onebox-body\"\u003e\n    \u003ch4\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://gist.github.com/JSandusky/340b09e9d104bae4c16b\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003ehttps://gist.github.com/JSandusky/340b09e9d104bae4c16b\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n  \u003ch5\u003eMotionControl.as\u003c/h5\u003e\n  \u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"AngelScript\"\u003e//=====================================\n//  MotionControl.as\n//  \n//  Controls animations based on the movements of a node:\n//      Automatically switches between strafing/forward/reverse/run/fall/jump\n//=====================================\n\n//=====================================\n//  class:      AnimSet\n//\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n    This file has been truncated. \u003ca href=\"https://gist.github.com/JSandusky/340b09e9d104bae4c16b\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003eshow original\u003c/a\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\n\u003c/p\u003e\n\n  \u003c/article\u003e\n\n  \u003cdiv class=\"onebox-metadata\"\u003e\n    \